    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-20T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-20T07:00:00-05:00" n="902"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d902">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5712: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hapgood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-20T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1919—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:57 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. Your 1805, October 20, 4 p.m., my 235, October 22, 3 p.m., 242, October 27,
                    3 p.m., 246, October 31, 10 a.m.<note n="25" xml:id="d902fn25">Last three not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Danish Foreign Office transmits following reply: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs states that he deems it
                            beneath his dignity to reply to question based on absurd rumor and <pb
                                facs="0888" n="776" xml:id="pg_776"/> mendacious and defamatory
                            articles in counter revolutionary newspapers. If the Danish Red Cross
                            really wishes to show its indignation in the name of humanity it can
                            find a rich field in drawing attention to the deeds of ferocity
                            committed by the criminal bands of <persName corresp="#p_DGAI"
                                >Denikin</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                            >Kolchak</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_YGNN1">Yudenitch</persName>
                            and [others].”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hapgood</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
